2.10 We recommended and management is amenable to direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Require the liquidation of the outstanding cash advance balances by the concerned officials and employees and if no action was taken by them, consider the withholding of their salaries, if warranted;
Refrain from granting additional cash advances to officials and employees with unliquidated balances;
Send notices to concerned officials and employees once the cash advance becomes overdue; and
Strictly comply with the provisions of the above-mentioned circular to 	avoid 	the sanctions stated thereon.

We recommended that Management: 

a. 	Establish a clear-cut policy on amount limitation, and procedural guidelines in the disbursement of funds for financial assistance in accordance with laws, ordinances, rules, and regulations; 

b. 	Evaluate the request for assistance to determine legality, reasonableness of cost, and conformity to prescribed laws, ordinances, rules, and regulations.

We recommended that Management: 

Issue a demand letter to notify the concerned officials, employees, and non-employees of their responsibility to settle their unliquidated cash advances and to employees who resigned/transferred to immediately cause the liquidation or settlement of the unliquidated cash advances;

Require the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer to strictly monitor the submission of liquidation reports on time to ensure timely accounting thereof to avoid an undue accumulation of outstanding cash advances; 

Refrain from approving succeeding cash advances unless the previous cash advances are fully accounted for and settled.

