Recommendations:
We required the Management to:
1). Submit to the office of the auditor, for audit purposes and provide the Municipal Accountant, for recording purposes the following documents:
copy of Deed of Donation between Municipality of Medina and Gerald L. Lamayra;
b)   copy of duly notarized Deed Conditional of Donation between the Barangay Portulin and the Municipality of Medina including but not limited to Tax Declaration and Title, and a copy of duly notarized Deed of Usufruct between the Municipality of Medina and Bukidnon State University.
c)  copy of duly notarized MOA and Deed of Donation for the acceptance of Biodegradable Shredder, Rotary Drum Biodegradable Composer and Solar Powered 4G Network Camera Kit (CCTV) to the undersigned auditors, for audit purposes;
2). Provide the Secretary of the Sanggunian copies of said Deeds documents for permanent file, future references and in aid of its local legislation;
3).  Require the Municipal Assessor to provide the proper valuation of these donated real properties as the basis for the municipal accountant in recording in the books of accounts.
4.) We also recommended that the SB require its Oversight Committee to review whether or not that the Resolutions authorizing the Municipal Mayor to enter into contract/obligation/MOAs including the above Donations that binds the Municipality has been complied with as a measure of checks and balance. Finally, we recommended that the SB shall pass a resolution requiring the Sanggunian Secretary and/or Municipal Librarian  to be  the repository of all perfected MOAs, Deed of Donation, Deed of Sale and other conveyances and agreements of similar in nature.

In compliance with COA Circular No. 2012-001, we recommended that Management:

Monitor the Project Implementation of the identified projects under the 20% Local Development Fund released to the 14 Barangay of the Municipality;

Submit copy of the MOA/Trust Agreement and copy of the approved Program of Works;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to see to it that previous projects were already liquidated before a new fund transfer shall be made.

